    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Hey there, CNN.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I know you’ve had a rough go of it the last few years. To half the country, your name is synonymous with “fake news,” and everything you say is not to be taken with a grain of salt so much as a pillar of it. To a good chunk of the other half, you embody everything that is wrong with corporate journalism in the institutional pursuit of carving out a neutral zone between the FOXes and MSNBCs of the world. You were a particular punching bag of the former president, and while I’ve not entirely forgiven you for the <a href="https://www.seattletimes.com/opinion/cnn-and-jeff-zucker-helped-give-us-trump/" target="_self">role</a> you <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5O-87CAAImk" target="_self">played</a> in <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OGFff6N0Bsg" target="_self">empowering</a> him in the first place, I can only imagine the toll it’s taken in your offices and how bizarre the comedown must be.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I know, I know. There’s no ethical blah blah blah under bleh bleh bleh. But, look, I don’t need you to be ProPublica out here. And I think that for all the holograms and the chyrons and the flashy effects, you’ve still got good people trying to do good work out there, in the name of a 1st Amendment freedom every bit as important as assembly, religion, or speech.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">(You also let Rick Santorum <a href="https://www.avclub.com/cnn-finally-gets-around-to-firing-rick-santorum-1846948211" target="_self">hang around for a minute</a>, but hey. Let he who has not sinned, amirite?)</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">So what I’m about to say doesn’t come from a place of love, <em>per se</em>, but more of constructive criticism. And I hope you’ll take it to heart.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
